data.title: Masters Of Jazz, Vol. 11
data.meta_description:
Masters Of Jazz, Vol. 11 by Billie Holiday, released 18 March 2020

1. Do Nothing Till You Hear from Me
2. I'll Get By
3. Billie's Blues, Pt. 1
4. All of Me, Pt. 1
5. The Man I Love
6. You Better Go Now
7. Miss Brown to You, Pt. 1
8. Lover Man, Pt. 1
9. I Wonder Where Our Love Has Gone
10. I Love My Man
11. You Ain't Gonna Bother Me No More
12. Good Morning Heartache
13. You're Driving Me Crazy, Pt. 1
14. Maybe You'll Be There
15. Billie's Blues, Pt. 2
16. Lover Man, Pt. 2
17. Them There Eyes
18. My Man
19. I Cover the Waterfront
20. Crazy He Calls Me
21. Lover Come Back to Me
22. Detour Ahead
23. Strange Fruit
24. You're Driving Me Crazy, Pt. 2
25. Ain't Nobody's Business If I Do
26. All of Me, Pt. 2
27. I Loves You Porgy
28. Miss Brown to You, Pt. 2

This compilation features Billie Holiday singing many classic standards including Strange Fruit, Lover Man, The Man I Love, All of Me, I Loves You Porgy, I Love My Man, Them There Eyes and Do Nothing ‘Til You Hear From Me. Her musicians on these sessions, recorded between 1944 - 1951 include Roy Eldridge (tp), Hot Lips Page (tp), Coleman Hawkins (ts), Jack Teagarden (tb), Art Tatum (p), Teddy Wilson (p), Jimmy Rowles (p), Oscar Pettiford (b) and “Big” Sid Catlett (dr). *”And at many points the remark of Frank Sinatra comes to mind, that Billie Holiday was the singer who taught him the most about communicating the emotional contents of a song” - *from the new liner notes by Thorbjørn Sjøgren
data.text: Storyville Records is Europe’s oldest independent jazz label. It releases a rich variety of jazz, blues and related musical genres, often accompanied by authoritative notes and rare extras. This iconic label was founded in 1952 in Denmark and today continues to augment its historic catalogue of recordings made by American jazz and blues legends with new releases from contemporary jazz artists. ... more
